(450923,'ede970a5-71c6-55cb-ad91-d654f86ea3d8','The Stack Overflow Podcast','For more than a dozen years, the Stack Overflow Podcast has been exploring what it means to be a software developer and how the art and practice of programming is changing our world. From Rails to React, from Java to Node.js, join the Stack home team for conversations with fascinating guests to help you understand how technology is made and where it‚Äôs headed.','The Stack Overflow Podcast','Stack Overflow','https://feeds.simplecast.com/XA_851k3','https://stackoverflow.blog/podcast/','https://image.simplecastcdn.com/images/f0fdf349-149b-42f9-95d0-8ddf72185776/02a60604-9d42-4ec4-a716-8d9a2942f79c/3000x3000/stack-overflow-podcast-1080x1080.jpg?aid=rss_feed','https://image.simplecastcdn.com/images/f0fdf349-149b-42f9-95d0-8ddf72185776/02a60604-9d42-4ec4-a716-8d9a2942f79c/3000x3000/stack-overflow-podcast-1080x1080.jpg?aid=rss_feed',0,723,'102;;;77;;;78;;;9;;;13'),
(599944,'7d453850-8e34-57b4-8558-08ddd8ba8e29','DevQuestions with Tim Corey','<p>I am Tim Corey. I teach coding online and my inbox is full of questions from current and future developers. I wish I could sit down with each of you and share the answers I know will help you go further, faster in the world of development. This podcast is the next best thing. On this podcast, I will answer the biggest questions people are asking! Send us to your suggestion for a future Dev Questions at https://suggestions.iamtimcorey.com/ To keep the podcast coming, like, subscribe, rate, and share it with your friends and colleagues. See why thousands of students have chosen to learn to think and code like a professional developer at www.iamtimcorey.com.¬†</p>','Tim Corey','Tim Corey','https://feeds.buzzsprout.com/1183862.rss','https://iamtimcorey.buzzsprout.com','https://storage.buzzsprout.com/c9iocudx16ij4espsgtoj5qbq8sk?.jpg','https://storage.buzzsprout.com/c9iocudx16ij4espsgtoj5qbq8sk?.jpg',0,218,'20;;;102;;;21'),
(853158,'3d194fe1-15f7-5a02-9dba-8d8decab8ff7','Soft Skills Engineering','It takes more than great code to be a great engineer. Soft Skills Engineering is a weekly advice podcast for software developers about the non-technical stuff that goes into being a great software developer.','Jamison Dance and Dave Smith','Jamison Dance and Dave Smith','https://softskills.audio/feed.xml','https://softskills.audio/','https://download.softskills.audio/sse-cover-art.png','https://download.softskills.audio/sse-cover-art.png',0,421,'102');
