('1f4ebfdc-19f6-45b1-83c5-8468166bef79',450923,'Spreading the gospel of Python',replace('<p><a href="https://alsweigart.com/">Al Sweigert</a> is the author of <a href="https://automatetheboringstuff.com/"><i>Automate the Boring Stuff with Python</i></a> and many other books about programming. You can read them all for free <a href="https://inventwithpython.com/">here</a>.</p><p>His <a href="https://scrollart.org/">scroll art</a> project introduces beginners to programming by letting them turn loops and print() into animated ASCII art.</p><p>Al joined us from a retreat at the Brooklyn, NY-based <a href="https://www.recurse.com/">Recurse Center</a>, which offers free, self-directed retreats for programmers. Learn how to apply <a href="https://www.recurse.com/apply">here</a>.</p><p><a href="https://us.pycon.org/2024/">PyCon US 2024</a> is May 15-23, 2024, in Pittsburgh, Pennsylvania.</p><p>Connect with Al through <a href="https://alsweigart.com/">his website</a>.</p><p>Shoutout to user <a href="https://stackoverflow.com/users/18300/alex-s">Alex. S.</a>, who asked Stack Overflow‚Äôs most popular Python question <i>ever</i>: <a href="https://stackoverflow.com/questions/231767/what-does-the-yield-keyword-do-in-python">What does the "yield" keyword do in Python?</a>. It‚Äôs helped 3.3 million people and counting.</p>\n','\n',char(10)),'https://stackoverflow.blog/podcast/','https://chrt.fm/track/G8F1AF/pdrl.fm/c28362/injector.simplecastaudio.com/6fa1d34c-502b-4abf-bd82-483804006e0b/episodes/a4932852-8ad2-4ef1-bb51-74f1b662cfdb/audio/128/default.mp3?aid=rss_feed&awCollectionId=6fa1d34c-502b-4abf-bd82-483804006e0b&awEpisodeId=a4932852-8ad2-4ef1-bb51-74f1b662cfdb&feed=XA_851k3',1715660400,1508,0,701,0),
('03db8eaf-21dc-4ad5-8022-60d81a6ebd43',450923,'Between hyper-focus and burnout: Developing with ADHD',replace('<p>Read Eira‚Äôs two-part series about developers with ADHD <a href="https://stackoverflow.blog/2023/12/26/developer-with-adhd-youre-not-alone/">here</a> and <a href="https://stackoverflow.blog/2023/06/05/what-developers-with-adhd-want-you-to-know/">here</a>.</p><p>Chris recommends that devs with ADHD employ a ‚Äúsecond brain‚Äù to help them track and remember information. <a href="https://stackoverflow.blog/2022/10/03/two-heads-are-better-than-one-what-second-brains-say-about-how-developers-work/">Read Eira‚Äôs article</a> on what second brains reveal about how we work.</p><p>A few years back Chris joined us to talk about the most lightweight web ‚Äúframework‚Äù around: VanillaJS. <a href="https://stackoverflow.blog/2021/12/21/podcast-402-teaching-developers-about-the-most-lightweight-web-framework-around-vanillajs/">Listen to the episode</a>.</p><p>Chris offers <a href="https://gomakethings.com/courses/">classes and workshops for front-end developers</a>, plus <a href="https://adhdftw.com/">daily advice for developers with ADHD</a>.</p><p>Connect with Chris through <a href="https://gomakethings.com/">his website</a> or <a href="https://twitter.com/ChrisFerdinandi">social media</a>.</p>\n','\n',char(10)),'https://stackoverflow.blog/podcast/','https://chrt.fm/track/G8F1AF/pdrl.fm/c28362/injector.simplecastaudio.com/6fa1d34c-502b-4abf-bd82-483804006e0b/episodes/1169c52e-b1e8-4c82-8568-e73ef98e25f9/audio/128/default.mp3?aid=rss_feed&awCollectionId=6fa1d34c-502b-4abf-bd82-483804006e0b&awEpisodeId=1169c52e-b1e8-4c82-8568-e73ef98e25f9&feed=XA_851k3',1715314800,1749,0,700,0),
('5e03808a-26b6-4426-9c46-1f6774a1be15',450923,'Reshaping the future of API platforms',replace('<p><a href="https://konghq.com/">Kong</a> is a cloud-native API gateway. Find them on <a href="https://github.com/Kong/">GitHub</a>.</p><p><a href="https://stackoverflow.blog/2023/03/13/building-an-api-is-half-the-battle-qa-with-marco-palladino-from-kong/">We last spoke with Marco</a> in 2023. inf</p><p>Connect with Marco on <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/marcopalladino/">LinkedIn</a>.</p><p>Congrats to <a href="https://stackoverflow.com/help/badges/28/famous-question">Famous Question badge</a> winner <a href="https://stackoverflow.com/users/11778370/mjbradford7">mjbradford7</a> on <a href="https://stackoverflow.com/questions/61434127/how-to-re-render-one-component-from-another-in-react">How to re-render one component from another in React</a>.</p>\n','\n',char(10)),'https://stackoverflow.blog/podcast/','https://chrt.fm/track/G8F1AF/pdrl.fm/c28362/injector.simplecastaudio.com/6fa1d34c-502b-4abf-bd82-483804006e0b/episodes/a0b8dfa3-7ce7-4632-a4df-8c3867d9ce17/audio/128/default.mp3?aid=rss_feed&awCollectionId=6fa1d34c-502b-4abf-bd82-483804006e0b&awEpisodeId=a0b8dfa3-7ce7-4632-a4df-8c3867d9ce17&feed=XA_851k3',1715055600,1588,0,699,0),
('fec95d6b-9fd8-4c11-96cd-ae4a1bb5202d',450923,'OverflowAI and the holy grail of search',replace('<p><a href="https://stackoverflow.co/teams/ai/?utm_medium=referral&utm_source=blog&utm_campaign=teams-overflowai-launch">OverflowAI</a> is a GenAI-powered add-on for Stack Overflow for Teams that does the heavy lifting of discovering and distilling information into a coherent answer. It encompasses three modules: Enhanced Search, an upgraded search experience; Stack Overflow for Visual Studio Code, an IDE extension; and Auto-Answer App for Slack, which automates access to essential team knowledge.¬†</p><p>Read about <a href="https://stackoverflow.blog/2024/05/14/introducing-overflowai-a-new-era-of-community-driven-ai-at-stack-overflow/">why OverflowAI is a big step toward integrating GenAI offerings into knowledge communities</a> and dig into <a href="https://stackoverflow.co/teams/resources/introducing-overflowai/">what‚Äôs launching and why it‚Äôs valuable</a>.</p><p>Connect with Ash on <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/ash-zade-19579a1a/?originalSubdomain=ca">LinkedIn</a>.</p><p>Big props to Stack Overflow user <a href="https://stackoverflow.com/users/5563616/jennifer-m">Jennifer M.</a>, who earned <i>both</i> a <a href="https://stackoverflow.com/help/badges/22/great-question">Great Question badge</a> <i>and</i> a <a href="https://stackoverflow.com/help/badges/28/famous-question">Famous Question badge</a> by wondering <a href="https://stackoverflow.com/questions/34477547/how-to-combine-the-sequence-of-objects-in-jq-into-one-object">How to combine the sequence of objects in jq into one object?</a>.</p>\n','\n',char(10)),'https://stackoverflow.blog/podcast/','https://chrt.fm/track/G8F1AF/pdrl.fm/c28362/injector.simplecastaudio.com/6fa1d34c-502b-4abf-bd82-483804006e0b/episodes/82d2ee35-8997-4c3d-aa5a-30c6d7ce133f/audio/128/default.mp3?aid=rss_feed&awCollectionId=6fa1d34c-502b-4abf-bd82-483804006e0b&awEpisodeId=82d2ee35-8997-4c3d-aa5a-30c6d7ce133f&feed=XA_851k3',17159