('d815c0f3-352d-4a1a-96e7-1175a62ab53e',450923,'The reverse mullett model of software engineering',replace('<p>If you‚Äôve been laid off or you‚Äôre just sweating the possibility, <a href="https://stackoverflow.blog/2022/12/05/just-laid-off-nervous-about-possible-layoffs-heres-what-to-do/">here‚Äôs what to do</a>.¬†</p><p>Check out <a href="https://stackoverflow.blog/2023/10/26/hopping-instead-of-hustling-survey-tells-us-how-developers-are-taking-care-of-business/">the results</a> of our last job market survey.¬†</p><p>Connect with Patrick on <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/patrick-carlile-48181b3/">LinkedIn</a>.</p><p>Shoutout to <a href="https://stackoverflow.com/users/1099089/stevenkucera">stevenkucera</a>, who earned a <a href="https://stackoverflow.com/help/badges/36/stellar-question">Stellar Question badge</a> with <a href="https://stackoverflow.com/questions/27791532/how-do-i-create-a-global-mutable-singleton">How do I create a global, mutable singleton?</a>.</p>\n','\n',char(10)),'https://stackoverflow.blog/podcast/','https://chrt.fm/track/G8F1AF/pdrl.fm/c28362/injector.simplecastaudio.com/6fa1d34c-502b-4abf-bd82-483804006e0b/episodes/3fb6317b-92fb-4c4b-8739-fa02f87a77d2/audio/128/default.mp3?aid=rss_feed&awCollectionId=6fa1d34c-502b-4abf-bd82-483804006e0b&awEpisodeId=3fb6317b-92fb-4c4b-8739-fa02f87a77d2&feed=XA_851k3',1714710000,1381,0,698,0),
('82200a19-7cac-41d1-8967-bee374d16993',450923,'Supporting the world‚Äôs most-used database engine through 2050',replace('<p><a href="https://www.sqlite.org/index.html">SQLite</a> is the most used database engine in the world.¬†</p><p>Stop by the <a href="https://sqlite.org/forum/forum">forum</a> or explore the <a href="https://www.sqlite.org/docs.html">docs</a>.</p><p>Devs have pledged to support SQLite <a href="https://www.sqlite.org/lts.html">through the year 2050</a>.¬†</p><p>The developer with a team of three, all of them himself at different points in time, was <a href="https://stackoverflow.blog/2021/12/31/700000-lines-of-code-20-years-and-one-developer-how-dwarf-fortress-is-built/#wp-comment-2084959">Tarn Adams of Dwarf Fortress</a> fame.¬†</p><p>On Stack Overflow, 1.2 million people have found the answer to <a href="https://stackoverflow.com/questions/82875/how-can-i-list-the-tables-in-a-sqlite-database-file-that-was-opened-with-attach">How can I list the tables in a SQLite database file that was opened with ATTACH?</a>.¬†</p>\n','\n',char(10)),'https://stackoverflow.blog/podcast/','https://chrt.fm/track/G8F1AF/pdrl.fm/c28362/injector.simplecastaudio.com/6fa1d34c-502b-4abf-bd82-483804006e0b/episodes/b7de52b9-ddc1-47f2-b0d4-a79a20853fbc/audio/128/default.mp3?aid=rss_feed&awCollectionId=6fa1d34c-502b-4abf-bd82-483804006e0b&awEpisodeId=b7de52b9-ddc1-47f2-b0d4-a79a20853fbc&feed=XA_851k3',1714105200,1729,0,696,0),
('c8025d8f-667c-4eec-b2c5-bd27d8938ec7',450923,'Is GenAI the next dot-com bubble?',replace('<p>Meta‚Äôs open-source Llama 3 model puts Meta‚Äôs AI assistant <a href="https://www.theverge.com/2024/4/18/24133808/meta-ai-assistant-llama-3-chatgpt-openai-rival">head-to-head with ChatGPT</a>.</p><p>Stability AI <a href="https://www.theverge.com/2024/4/18/24133996/stability-ai-lay-off-emad-mostaque">laid off</a> 10% of its workforce, the first major AI foundation model to reduce its workforce since the advent of generative AI.</p><p>Is the dot-com bubble a cautionary tale for AI enthusiasts? <a href="https://www.npr.org/podcasts/381444600/marketplace">Listen to the episode</a> of Marketplace from NPR.</p><p><a href="https://philosophy.stackexchange.com/questions/112021/does-the-success-of-ai-large-language-models-support-wittgensteins-position-t">Do LLMs support Wittgenstein‚Äôs position that ‚Äúmeaning is use‚Äù?</a> That depends whether you‚Äôre talking pre or post <i>Tractatus</i>, of course.</p><p>TikTok wouldn‚Äôt lie to you: you really can <a href="https://www.technologyreview.com/2022/10/31/1062370/how-to-befriend-a-crow-crowtok-tiktok/">make friends with your local crows</a>. Eira‚Äôs proven method for befriending crows: Feed them dry cat food on a consistent schedule, so they learn you‚Äôre reliable, and watch them eat, so they grok that you are feeding them intentionally.</p><p>Stack Overflow user <a href="https://stackoverflow.com/users/2133484/arman-ordookhani">Arman Ordookhani</a> received a well-deserved <a href="https://stackoverflow.com/help/badges/8842/lifeboat">Lifeboat badge</a> for telling nearly 30,000 people <a href="https://stackoverflow.com/questions/47979203/how-to-free-memory-in-go">How to free memory in go</a>.</p>\n','\n',char(10)),'https://stackoverflow.blog/podcast/','https://chrt.fm/track/G8F1AF/pdrl.fm/c28362/injector.simplecastaudio.com/6fa1d34c-502b-4abf-bd82-483804006e0b/episodes/aafa5c12-9b76-4561-a3cc-88de5871f053/audio/128/default.mp3