('1d7aed91-4b15-4f56-a376-baecba1c6c5d',450923,'Diverting more backdoor disasters',replace('<p>ICYMI: A <a href="https://cybernews.com/editorial/xz-linux-backdoor-explained/">backdoor</a> in XZ, a popular open-source compression utility, highlights the risks of relying on open-source software maintained by small teams. Read more about the cyberattack <a href="https://boehs.org/node/everything-i-know-about-the-xz-backdoor?fbclid=IwAR12WI8Q5mlVTfR96aOj6B6Xm2ulAi---eLS8LelU3w661OlTh70ldF4a-A_aem_ARc8um12YBHJx9eaZlOkyCEYoxlaWtptRPh9w_2mgUOvHDWfOR8YTxwfJANYA96rEoU3Sq2DH0b3EDt6KUDtLQ95">here</a>.</p><p>Apple‚Äôs new LLM, <a href="https://appleinsider.com/articles/24/04/09/apples-new-ai-model-could-help-siri-see-how-ios-apps-work">Ferret</a>, could help Siri understand the user interfaces of mobile displays, potentially expanding the capabilities of Apple‚Äôs digital assistant.¬†</p><p>Shoutout to Stack Overflow user <a href="https://stackoverflow.com/users/1569632/cheese1756">cheese1756</a>, who earned a <a href="https://stackoverflow.com/help/badges/22/great-question">Great Question badge</a> by asking <a href="https://stackoverflow.com/questions/15721373/how-do-i-ensure-that-whitespace-is-preserved-in-markdown">How do I ensure that whitespace is preserved in Markdown?</a>.</p>\n','\n',char(10)),'https://stackoverflow.blog/podcast/','https://chrt.fm/track/G8F1AF/pdrl.fm/c28362/injector.simplecastaudio.com/6fa1d34c-502b-4abf-bd82-483804006e0b/episodes/0d0fddba-1468-4ef8-b775-19a1bb08faac/audio/128/default.mp3?aid=rss_feed&awCollectionId=6fa1d34c-502b-4abf-bd82-483804006e0b&awEpisodeId=0d0fddba-1468-4ef8-b775-19a1bb08faac&feed=XA_851k3',1712895600,1116,0,691,0),
('ff6f1e6c-a295-46d8-87ab-d9e377f45a56',450923,'Why the creator of Node.js¬Æ created a new JavaScript runtime',replace('<p><a href="https://nodejs.org/en">Node.js</a>¬Æ is an open-source JavaScript runtime environment.</p><p><a href="https://deno.com/">Deno</a> is an open-source JavaScript, TypeScript, and WebAssembly runtime. Explore the <a href="https://docs.deno.com/runtime/manual">quick start</a> or check out <a href="https://examples.deno.land/">Deno by example</a>, a collection of annotated examples of how to use Deno.</p><p><a href="https://jsr.io/">JSR</a> is an open-source package registry for JavaScript and TypeScript.</p><p>Keep up to date with Ryan on <a href="https://github.com/ry">GitHub</a> or <a href="https://tinyclouds.org/">his blog</a>.</p><p>Shoutout to Stack Overflow user <a href="https://stackoverflow.com/users/849055/squadrons">Squadrons</a>, who earned a <a href="https://stackoverflow.com/help/badges/22/great-question">Great Question badge</a> by asking for a <a href="https://stackoverflow.com/questions/6838104/pure-javascript-method-to-wrap-content-in-a-div">Pure javascript method to wrap content in a div</a>.</p><p>Chapters:</p><p>00:00: Introduction and Background</p><p>01:08: Creating Node.js</p><p>05:00: JavaScript on the Server Side</p><p>07:23: Impact of Node.js</p><p>09:18: Edge Function System</p><p>12:13: Protecting Against Malicious Use</p><p>16:02: JSR: Alternative to NPM</p><p>31:01: JSR and its Stage</p><p>34:20: Future of JavaScript</p><p>36:19: Closing and Shoutouts</p>\n','\n',char(10)),'https://stackoverflow.blog/podcast/','https://chrt.fm/track/G8F1AF/pdrl.fm/c28362/injector.simplecastaudio.com/6fa1d34c-502b-4abf-bd82-483804006e0b/episodes/c05979b9-8406-4d1b-bbbc-535659624ce9/audio/128/default.mp3?aid=rss_feed&awCollectionId=6fa1d34c-502b-4abf-bd82-483804006e0b&awEpisodeId=c05979b9-8406-4d1b-bbbc-535659624ce9&feed=XA_851k3',1710822000,1923,0,682,0),
