('3d18df4d-564d-419c-9760-664880bad411',450923,'Optimizing both hardware and software for GenAI',replace('<p>SPONSORED BY INTEL</p><p>¬†</p><p>Ryan and Ben chat with Raymond Lo, AI software evangelist at Intel, about the AI PC, the software that powers AI breakthroughs, and optimizing hardware and software in unison to improve generative AI performance. Bonus: what‚Äôs the difference between a GPU optimized for graphics and a VPU or NPU optimized for AI?</p><p>¬†</p><p><strong>Episode notes</strong></p><p>¬†</p><p>If you‚Äôre interested in trying any of the demos that Raymond talked about, check out Intel‚Äôs OpenVINO notebooks.</p><p>¬†</p><p>Learn more about Intel‚Äôs Edge AI resources here.</p><p>¬†</p><p>Raymond previously wrote about enhancing image and video resolution using OpenVINO.</p><p>¬†</p><p>You can reach out to Raymond Lo on LinkedIn.</p><p>¬†</p><p>Congrats to Lifeboat badge winner, Andrey Korneyev, for saving the question, How can I delete specific nodes from an XElement?</p>\n','\n',char(10)),'https://stackoverflow.blog/podcast/','https://chrt.fm/track/G8F1AF/pdrl.fm/c28362/injector.simplecastaudio.com/6fa1d34c-502b-4abf-bd82-483804006e0b/episodes/9e2a78e6-48c4-4939-af0f-9c5a198edb88/audio/128/default.mp3?aid=rss_feed&awCollectionId=6fa1d34c-502b-4abf-bd82-483804006e0b&awEpisodeId=9e2a78e6-48c4-4939-af0f-9c5a198edb88&feed=XA_851k3',1709097300,1572,0,675,0),
