('fee0dc47-90dc-48f0-a4f3-8480aee8087d',450923,'Exploring the inclusive tech revolution',replace('<p>Find out why others have <a href="https://www.shell.com/careers/letters-to-the-future/why-i-joined-shell.html">joined Shell</a>.</p><p>If you want to experience what being a developer at one of the world‚Äôs largest energy companies looks like, <a href="https://www.shell.com/careers/information-technology.html">they‚Äôre hiring</a>.</p><p>Great question, <a href="https://stackoverflow.com/users/1675347/alexander-myshov">Alexander Myshov</a>! This badge was awarded for <a href="https://stackoverflow.com/questions/44030645/are-arrow-functions-faster-more-performant-lighter-than-ordinary-standalone-f">Are arrow functions faster (more performant, lighter) than ordinary standalone function declaration in v8?</a></p><p>Reach out to Maya on <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/mayasellon/">LinkedIn</a>.</p>\n','\n',char(10)),'https://stackoverflow.blog/podcast/','https://chrt.fm/track/G8F1AF/pdrl.fm/c28362/injector.simplecastaudio.com/6fa1d34c-502b-4abf-bd82-483804006e0b/episodes/9adae93c-9f78-4c30-a232-ffd342d241db/audio/128/default.mp3?aid=rss_feed&awCollectionId=6fa1d34c-502b-4abf-bd82-483804006e0b&awEpisodeId=9adae93c-9f78-4c30-a232-ffd342d241db&feed=XA_851k3',1707888000,1282,0,670,0),
('62c85ebb-d1cd-427e-8286-f54aea27a358',450923,'AI isn''t putting tech workers out of jobs, the stock price is',replace('<p>AI-generated code is ‚Äúnot equivalent to reliable and robust code, especially in the context of real-world software development,‚Äù according to <a href="https://arxiv.org/html/2308.10335v5">a new study</a> whose title got our attention.</p><p><a href="https://www.nytimes.com/2024/01/30/business/dealbook/tech-layoffs.html">Tech layoffs continue</a> in the wake of the pandemic hiring boom, sending some share prices into the sky.</p><p>Take a look at <a href="https://www.technologyreview.com/2023/12/06/1084457/ai-assistants-copilot-changing-code-software-development-github-openai/">how AI coding assistants are already changing</a> the way code is made.</p><p>Shoutout to Stack Overflow user <a href="https://stackoverflow.com/users/325418/nonopolarity">nonopolarity</a>, who earned a <a href="https://stackoverflow.com/help/badges/22/great-question">Great Question badge</a> by asking <a href="https://stackoverflow.com/questions/5280827/can-someone-explain-ssh-tunnel-in-a-simple-way">Can someone explain SSH tunnel in a simple way?</a>.</p>\n','\n',char(10)),'https://stackoverflow.blog/podcast/','https://chrt.fm/track/G8F1AF/pdrl.fm/c28362/injector.simplecastaudio.com/6fa1d34c-502b-4abf-bd82-483804006e0b/episodes/e0d2e1ab-318f-492a-936a-65d9ce7c133b/audio/128/default.mp3?aid=rss_feed&awCollectionId=6fa1d34c-502b-4abf-bd82-483804006e0b&awEpisodeId=e0d2e1ab-318f-492a-936a-65d9ce7c133b&feed=XA_851k3',1707196800,866,0,667,0),
('f395edef-9dd2-4e31-9c0b-3b76a3ef03f3',450923,'How to beat Doom in just 600 years',replace('<p>A theory explores how to <a href="https://80.lv/articles/you-can-play-doom-on-cells-potentially/">play DOOM inside a human cell</a>. Fair warning, you''ll need about 600 years to complete the game.</p><p>Looking for a good prompt builder to help you get the most out of your LLM? Try <a href="https://mitenmit.github.io/gpt/">this one</a> or explore <a href="https://www.futuretools.io/tools/prompt-vibes">this huge collection</a> of prompts.</p><p>Startup <a href="https://techcrunch.com/2024/01/31/twin-labs-automates-repetitive-tasks-by-letting-ai-take-over-your-mouse-cursor/">Twin Labs</a> wants to build a product that automates repetitive tasks by letting AI take over your cursor.</p><p>Harvard Medical School researchers published a study showing that the <a href="https://news.harvard.edu/gazette/story/2016/08/finding-biological-barcodes/">CRISPR system</a> can encode information in living cells ‚Äúas complex as a digitized image of a human hand.‚Äù <a href="https://news.harvard.edu/gazette/story/2017/07/taking-cells-out-to-the-movies-with-new-crispr-technology/">Read more</a>.</p><p>Three cheers for <a href="https://stackoverflow.com/users/10593/max-lybbert">Max Lybbert</a>, who earned a <a href="https://stackoverflow.com/help/badges/8842/lifeboat">Lifeboat badge</a> by answering <a href="https://stackoverflow.com/questions/9688305/python-faster-than-c-how-does-this-happen">Python faster than C++? How does this happen?</a>.</p>\n','\n',char(10)),'https://stackoverflow.blog/podcast/','https://chrt.fm/track/G8F1AF/pdrl.fm/c28362/injector.simplecastaudio.com/6fa1d34c-502b-4abf-bd82-483804006e0b/episodes/024fe975-502e-46a9-9bdc-b0bca6a09e01/audio/128/default.mp3?aid=rss_feed&awCollectionId=6fa1d34c-502b-4abf-bd82-483804006e0b&awEpisodeId=024fe975-502e-46a9-9bdc-b0bca6a09e01&feed=XA_851k3',1706851200,916,0,666,0),
('cec81b73-5ad9-4a60-8d1b-928f9e98fff9',450923,'Agile works great...to a certain size',replace('<p>The estate of the late comedian George Carlin is <a href="https://apnews.com/article/george-carlin-artificial-intelligence-special-lawsuit-39d64f728f7a6a621f25d3f4789acadd">suing</a> the creators of an hour-long AI-generated comedy special that mimics Carlin‚Äôs distinctive delivery and material. [<i>Ed. note: </i><a href="https://www.nytimes.com/2024/01/26/arts/carlin-lawsuit-ai-podcast-copyright.html"><i>not actually AI</i></a><i>, still lawsuit</i>.]</p><p>Prefer your AI more Freudo-Marxist? <a href="https://www.infiniteconversation.com/">Here‚Äôs a never-ending, AI-generated conversation</a> between Werner Herzog and Slavoj ≈Ωi≈æek. You‚Äôre welcome.</p><p>Google‚Äôs Bard surpassed GPT-4 to claim the second spot on the <a href="https://huggingface.co/spaces/lmsys/chatbot-arena-leaderboard">LMSYS Chatbot Arena Leaderboard</a>.</p><p>Agile development is faltering at big companies, and <a href="https://www.itpro.com/software/agile-development-is-fading-in-popularity-at-large-enterprises-and-developer-burnout-is-a-key-factor">a recent report</a> cites developer burnout as a factor. But maybe the problem lies in companies‚Äô (mis)understanding of agile.</p><p>Shoutout to Stack Overflow user <a href="https://stackoverflow.com/users/3425536/emil-laine">Emil Laine</a>, who earned a <a href="https://stackoverflow.com/help/badges/8842/lifeboat">Lifeboat badge</a> with their answer to <a href="https://stackoverflow.com/questions/36761734/how-can-i-include-all-of-the-c-standard-library-at-once">How can I include all of the C++ Standard Library at once?</a>.</p>\n','\n',char(10)),'https://stackoverflow.blog/podcast/','https://chrt.fm/track/G8F1AF/pdrl.fm/c28362/injector.simplecastaudio.com/6fa1d34c-502b-4abf-bd82-483804006e0b/episodes/7a69697b-b9f9-4979-88db-ff4fcf4d821d/audio/128/default.mp3?aid=rss_feed&awCollectionId=6fa1d34c-502b-4abf-bd82-483804006e0b&awEpisodeId=7a69697b-b9f9-4979-88db-ff4fcf4d821d&feed=XA_851k3',1706592000,913,0,664,0),
('c352c773-72e0-4308-bae2-83736451edfc',450923,'Inside Intuit''s generative AI system, GenOS',replace('<p>Intuit shares more about their generative AI operating system (GenOS) in <a href="https://medium.com/intuit-engineering/how-to-accelerate-development-velocity-in-the-genai-era-build-a-genos-e71ac2e17b82">this Medium blog</a>.¬†</p><p>Learn more about Intuit technology <a href="https://www.intuit.com/technology/?cid=dis_so_clicks_us_ttt-global_aw_fy24pod1%7Calltechaudience_link%7Cnone_intuit-talent">here</a>.</p><p>Congrats to Lifeboat badge winner <a href="https://stackoverflow.com/users/1436931/mohsin-naeem">Mohsin Naeem</a> for answering the question <a href="https://stackoverflow.com/questions/11327954/how-can-i-extract-metadata-from-an-mp3-file/11328221#11328221">How can I extract metadata from an MP3 file?</a></p><p>Connect with Merrin on <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/merrinkurian">LinkedIn</a> or <a href="https://twitter.com/merrinkurian">X</a>.¬†</p><p>Connect with Shivang on <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/shivangshah15/">LinkedIn</a>.</p>\n','\n',char(10)),'https://stackoverflow.blog/podcast/','https://chrt.fm/track/G8F1AF/pdrl.fm/c28362/injector.simplecastaudio.com/6fa1d34c-502b-4abf-bd82-483804006e0b/episodes/858c05e8-d76e-4706-a99f-f92e9ee6c965/audio/128/default.mp3?aid=rss_feed&awCollectionId=6fa1d34c-502b-4abf-bd82-483804006e0b&awEpisodeId=858c05e8-d76e-4706-a99f-f92e9ee6c965&feed=XA_851k3',1706678400,1867,0,665,0),
('30302bd9-92d9-43a1-b7e9-abc86ab345b1',450923,'Building a PDF larger than the known universe',replace('<p>Is it possible to <a href="https://alexwlchan.net/2024/big-pdf/">make a PDF bigger than Germany</a>? <a href="https://alexwlchan.net/files/2024/universe.pdf">Here‚Äôs one</a> larger than the known universe. As its creator says, ‚Äúit‚Äôs mostly empty space, but so is the universe.‚Äù</p><p>Massachusetts is <a href="https://fortune.com/2024/01/26/maura-healey-massachusetts-skills-based-hiring-no-college-degree-required/">leading the way</a> in the skills-based hiring revolution by eliminating degree requirements for state jobs.</p><p>Did you miss these deeply uncanny AI-generated food images, from the conjoined chickens to the macaroni and cheese rendered in shapes formerly unknown to geometry? Never fear; you can still see some <a href="https://www.businessinsider.com/instacart-deletes-ai-generated-food-images-2024-1">here</a>.</p><p>You may have forgotten about crypto (or at least tried), but <a href="https://arstechnica.com/science/2024/02/over-2-percent-of-the-uss-electricity-generation-now-goes-to-bitcoin/">more than 2%</a> of the United States‚Äôs electricity generation goes to large-scale crypto mining.</p><p>Stack Overflow user <a href="https://stackoverflow.com/users/1133019/jeff-allen">Jeff Allen</a> earned a <a href="https://stackoverflow.com/help/badges/22/great-question">Great Question badge</a> for <a href="https://stackoverflow.com/questions/14450384/create-a-vector-of-all-days-between-two-dates">Create a Vector of All Days Between Two Dates</a>, which has helped 85,000 <a href="https://stackoverflow.com/collectives/r-language">R users</a>.</p>\n','\n',char(10)),'https://stackoverflow.blog/podcast/','https://chrt.fm/track/G8F1AF/pdrl.fm/c28362/injector.simplecastaudio.com/6fa1d34c-502b-4abf-bd82-483804006e0b/episodes/2f8024ad-4996-45d4-86ba-beaedc5c56a9/audio/128/default.mp3?aid=rss_feed&awCollectionId=6fa1d34c-502b-4abf-bd82-483804006e0b&awEpisodeId=2f8024ad-4996-45d4-86ba-beaedc5c56a9&feed=XA_851k3',1707456000,1165,0,668,0),
('42324232-9ebd-4155-848f-1af1890540bd',450923,'Compression is understanding',replace('<p>Find out <a href="https://vickiboykis.com/2024/01/15/whats-new-with-ml-in-production/">what‚Äôs new with ML in production</a>.</p><p>Machine learning models must <a href="https://towardsdatascience.com/learn-to-unlearn-machines-6b0843dfc40f">learn to unlearn</a>.</p><p>Open-source game engine <a href="https://godotengine.org/">Godot</a> now has <a href="https://www.gamingonlinux.com/2024/01/godot-engine-gets-a-free-nintendo-switch-port-for-game-devs/">a free Nintendo Switch port for game developers</a>.</p><p>We‚Äôve previously hosted Godot cofounder and lead developer Juan Linietsky <a href="https://stackoverflow.blog/2023/02/28/the-open-source-game-engine-youve-been-waiting-for-godot-ep-542/">on the podcast</a>.</p><p>Stack Overflow user <a href="https://stackoverflow.com/users/4158603/areller">areller</a> earned a <a href="https://stackoverflow.com/help/badges/8842/lifeboat">Lifeboat badge</a> with their answer to <a href="https://stackoverflow.com/questions/41942950/how-to-call-a-destructor">How to call a destructor</a>.</p>\n','\n',char(10)),'https://stackoverflow.blog/podcast/','https://chrt.fm/track/G8F1AF/pdrl.fm/c28362/injector.simplecastaudio.com/6fa1d34c-502b-4abf-bd82-483804006e0b/episodes/1c1b40c8-4482-4d00-b5f4-253e9d0ca864/audio/128/default.mp3?aid=rss_feed&awCollectionId=6fa1d34c-502b-4abf-bd82-483804006e0b&awEpisodeId=1c1b40c8-4482-4d00-b5f4-253e9d0ca864&feed=XA_851k3',1706246400,993,0,663,0),
('7c0d04e4-99f1-48ba-8922-b5ad00424af1',450923,'Hacking the hamburger: How a pentester exposed holes in hundreds of fast-food chains',replace('<p>A white-hat hacker uncovered security vulnerabilities in an AI-powered hiring system used by fast-food chains and hourly employees around the world. <a href="https://mrbruh.com/chattr/">Read</a> the blog post or <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=BsrMMGEboXc&ab_channel=GitGuardian">watch</a> this explainer.</p><p><a href="https://github.com/ambulancja/mariposa">Mariposa</a> is a programming language with time travel.</p><p>Want to be an individual contributor (IC) who still amplifies the performance of everyone around you? Be a <a href="https://dev.37signals.com/the-radiating-programmer/">radiating programmer</a>.</p><p>Congratulations to <a href="https://stackoverflow.com/users/1418457/onmyway133">onmyway133</a>, winner of a <a href="https://stackoverflow.com/help/badges/36/stellar-question">Stellar Question badge</a> for <a href="https://stackoverflow.com/questions/47871868/what-does-the-suspend-function-mean-in-a-kotlin-coroutine">What does the suspend function mean in a Kotlin Coroutine?</a>.</p>\n','\n',char(10)),'https://stackoverflow.blog/podcast/','https://chrt.fm/track/G8F1AF/pdrl.fm/c28362/injector.simplecastaudio.com/6fa1d34c-502b-4abf-bd82-483804006e0b/episodes/606a59ac-d957-4bee-817e-a72a33926e8f/audio/128/default.mp3?aid=rss_feed&awCollectionId=6fa1d34c-502b-4abf-bd82-483804006e0b&awEpisodeId=606a59ac-d957-4bee-817e-a72a33926e8f&feed=XA_851k3',1705987200,1036,0,662,0),
('c536e6d1-c544-4329-9ce9-77c431799e33',450923,'Sending bugs back in time',replace('<p><a href="https://github.com/ambulancja/mariposa">Mariposa</a> is a toy programming language that has time travel as a primary feature. Bugs are a thing of the past (literally)!</p><p>Miss having a physical keyboard when thumb-typing on your phone? Well, <a href="https://twitter.com/MikeOBrienn/status/1745211879511998679">you‚Äôre in luck</a>.¬†</p><p>Over at CES, LG Electronics wants your devices to have ‚Äú<a href="https://venturebeat.com/ai/lg-embraces-the-age-of-affectionate-intelligence/">affectionate intelligence</a>.‚Äù Whatever it takes to make AI more human-centric and empathetic.</p><p>Omar used to work on the Backstage project at Spotify, so <a href="https://stackoverflow.blog/2022/12/21/i-spent-two-years-trying-to-do-what-backstage-does-for-free/">we quoted him</a> in our article on it.¬†</p><p>Now he works on personalization, including <a href="https://medium.com/the-sound-of-ai/spotifys-discover-weekly-explained-breaking-from-your-music-bubble-or-maybe-not-b506da144123">Discover Weekly</a>, which drops a new mixtape on you every Monday like a hipster with a crush.</p>\n','\n',char(10)),'https://stackoverflow.blog/podcast/','https://chrt.fm/track/G8F1AF/pdrl.fm/c28362/injector.simplecastaudio.com/6fa1d34c-502b-4abf-bd82-483804006e0b/episodes/4e494960-ef05-4d5c-98d7-c34e2aa6b07e/audio/128/default.mp3?aid=rss_feed&awCollectionId=6fa1d34c-502b-4abf-bd82-483804006e0b&awEpisodeId=4e494960-ef05-4d5c-98d7-c34e2aa6b07e&feed=XA_851k3',1705641600,1611,0,661,0),
('b39ed3b9-a3d5-484b-8114-cf4ac9c8c79f',450923,'Letting algorithms guide our path to the next great invention',replace('<p><a href="https://www.engadget.com/rabbit-r1-is-an-adorable-ai-powered-assistant-co-designed-by-teenage-engineering-001051537.html">Rabbit R1</a> is an AI-powered assistant you can keep in your pocket (but it‚Äôs not a phone).</p><p>How will AI impact scientific research? <a href="https://twitter.com/Microsoft/status/1744754722718769181">A new collaboration</a> between Microsoft and the Pacific Northwest National Laboratory is focused on energy storage solutions.</p><p>A <a href="https://arstechnica.com/information-technology/2024/01/at-senate-ai-hearing-news-executives-fight-against-fair-use-claims-for-ai-training-data/">US Senate hearing</a> questions whether tech companies should be allowed to train their AI models on content produced by journalists without paying licensing fees.</p><p>Learn <a href="https://www.drmoron.org/posts/mechanical-computer/">how to build a mechanical computer from Legos</a>.</p>\n','\n',char(10)),'https://stackoverflow.blog/podcast/','https://chrt.fm/track/G8F1AF/pdrl.fm/c28362/injector.simplecastaudio.com/6fa1d34c-502b-4abf-bd82-483804006e0b/episodes/53b24416-a851-4152-8bef-5f4117578d5c/audio/128/default.mp3?aid=rss_feed&awCollectionId=6fa1d34c-502b-4abf-bd82-483804006e0b&awEpisodeId=53b24416-a851-4152-8bef-5f4117578d5c&feed=XA_851k3',1705382400,1080,0,660,0),
('196515eb-8f20-4bb8-aa2d-627026ce8445',450923,'How long till we run out of fresh data to train the AI?',replace('<p>Will AI fundamentally change software development or just add some efficiencies around the edges? ¬†Surveys from Stack Overflow and <a href="https://www.zdnet.com/article/github-developer-survey-finds-92-of-programmers-using-ai-tools/">Github</a> find north of 70% have probably already tried using it and many incorporate it into their daily work through a helper in the IDE.¬†</p><p>It''s also worth reflecting a bit on the technology sectors that didn''t have as great a 2023: crypto, VR, and quantum computing still seem far from mainstream adoption.¬†</p><p>We dive a little into the half-life of skills, which <a href="https://hbr.org/2023/09/reskilling-in-the-age-of-ai">seem to be shrinking</a>, especially in IT. Got any resolutions to learn something new this year?</p><p>And what about the data we use for training? We highlight a comment from <a href="https://explorecourses.stanford.edu/instructor/kiank">Kian Katanforoosh</a>, a lecturer who helped create Stanford''s Deep Learning course with Andrew Ng, who says we''ll run out of high quality data as soon as 2030.</p><p>A big thanks and congrats to Stack Overflow user ¬†Corn3lius for helping to answer a question and being awarded a life boat badge: <a href="https://stackoverflow.com/questions/28615544/how-can-i-create-spoiler-text/28615681#28615681">How can I create spoiler text?</a></p>\n','\n',char(10)),'https://stackoverflow.blog/podcast/','https://chrt.fm/track/G8F1AF/pdrl.fm/c28362/injector.simplecastaudio.com/6fa1d34c-502b-4abf-bd82-483804006e0b/episodes/5b7e8bd0-4c62-42be-8ab2-35f7d40a2b60/audio/128/default.mp3?aid=rss_feed&awCollectionId=6fa1d34c-502b-4abf-bd82-483804006e0b&awEpisodeId=5b7e8bd0-4c62-42be-8ab2-35f7d40a2b60&feed=XA_851k3',1704431100,1292,0,657,0),
('ecddc9e4-1a46-4f50-ada4-f56bdaad91fa',450923,'How to build a role-playing video game in 24 hours',replace('<p>Now you know: The human body can serve as a resonance chamber for <a href="https://physics.stackexchange.com/questions/101913/why-does-a-remote-car-key-work-when-held-to-your-head-body">remote car keys</a>, effectively extending their range.</p><p>A hackathon team used GenAI can create a fully playable D&D-style game in <a href="https://meditations.metavert.io/p/semantic-programming-and-software">just one day</a>.</p><p>Skybox AI from <a href="https://www.blockadelabs.com/">Blockade Labs</a> allows users to generate 360¬∞ skybox experiences from text prompts.</p><p>A significant advancement in the brain-computer interfaces (BCI) space: <a href="https://openreview.net/pdf?id=WaLI8slhLw">a novel framework called DeWave</a> integrates ‚Äúdiscrete encoding sequences into open-vocabulary EEG-to-text translation tasks‚Äù without the need for ‚Äúeye-tracking fixations or event markers to segment brain dynamics into word-level features.‚Äù</p><p>Shoutout to Stack Overflow user <a href="https://stackoverflow.com/users/2381544/vineeth-chitteti">Vineeth Chitteti</a>, who earned a <a href="https://meta.stackoverflow.com/help/badges/33/favorite-question">Favorite Question badge</a> with <a href="https://stackoverflow.com/questions/49612412/kubenetes-is-it-possible-to-hit-multiple-pods-with-a-single-request-in-kubernet">Is it possible to hit multiple pods with a single request in Kubernetes cluster?</a>.</p>\n','\n',char(10)),'https://stackoverflow.blog/podcast/','https://chrt.fm/track/G8F1AF/pdrl.fm/c28362/injector.simplecastaudio.com/6fa1d34c-502b-4abf-bd82-483804006e0b/episodes/e6b65a7b-237e-4818-8725-c6643d5d8afe/audio/128/default.mp3?aid=rss_feed&awCollectionId=6fa1d34c-502b-4abf-bd82-483804006e0b&awEpisodeId=e6b65a7b-237e-4818-8725-c6643d5d8afe&feed=XA_851k3',1705036800,854,0,659,0),
('83b55652-185b-4a5d-9451-7f3662d1e2f7',450923,'Maximum Glitch: How to break Tetris',replace('<p>Willis Gibson, 13, closed out 2023 by becoming the first person to <a href="https://www.fastcompany.com/91005769/13-year-old-gamer-beats-tetris">officially beat</a> the original Nintendo version of Tetris. Here‚Äôs <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=GuJ5UuknsHU&ab_channel=aGameScout">how he did it</a>.</p><p>Want to understand the code that caused the ultimate killscreen? Watch this great <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=BpEcjdr_YDo&ab_channel=HydrantDude">explainer</a> from HydrantDude.</p><p>The 2023 film <a href="https://time.com/6266810/tetris-movie-apple-tv-true-story/"><i>Tetris</i></a> is based on the true story of the legal battle to license the game.</p><p>Is the era of the robot butler upon us? <a href="https://mobile-aloha.github.io/">Mobile ALOHA</a> is a low-cost and whole-body teleoperation system for data collection. Check out some of what it <a href="https://twitter.com/zipengfu/status/1742973258528612724">can do</a>.</p><p>Explore the questions and answers on the <a href="https://math.stackexchange.com/">Mathematics Stack Exchange</a>.</p>\n','\n',char(10)),'https://stackoverflow.blog/podcast/','https://chrt.fm/track/G8F1AF/pdrl.fm/c28362/injector.simplecastaudio.com/6fa1d34c-502b-4abf-bd82-483804006e0b/episodes/608b5dc3-ad03-4eac-a040-1d906bd72c0a/audio/128/default.mp3?aid=rss_feed&awCollectionId=6fa1d34c-502b-4abf-bd82-483804006e0b&awEpisodeId=608b5dc3-ad03-4eac-a040-1d906bd72c0a&feed=XA_851k3',1704777600,1097,0,658,0),
('b4e11b19-8d43-42fd-bb34-a1b23d848a49',450923,'He created Stanford''s Deep Learning class. Programmers will need to learn faster',replace('<p>Along with his work at Stanford, Katanforoosh is a founding member of deeplearning.ai and co-created the Deep Learning Specialization on Coursera.¬†</p><p>He believes the rapidly expanding capabilities of AI will mean that humans, and especially programmers, will need to learn new skills faster than ever. This doesn''t mean machines are going to take our jobs. Rather, with the assistance of AI, humans will become far more capable, learning faster and mastering more domains.¬†</p><p>Not surprisingly, Katanforoosh has built his business with the goal of addressing this issue. Workera aims to help companies identify where their employees lack skills and provide them with personalized instruction that can quickly bring them up to the next level.</p><p>You can find Kian on <a href="https://twitter.com/kiankatan?lang=en">Twitter</a>, <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/kiankatan/">LinkedIn</a>, and <a href="https://explorecourses.stanford.edu/instructor/kiank">Stanford''s website</a>.¬†</p><p>Thanks to Stack Overflow user PaxDiablo, who was awarded a Life Boat badge for providing a great answer to the question: <a href="https://stackoverflow.com/questions/29375785/first-month-of-quarter-given-month-in-python/29381448#29381448">Given ¬†a month in numeric form, how do you find the first month of its respective quarter?¬†</a></p><p>¬†</p>\n','\n',char(10)),'https://stackoverflow.blog/podcast/','https://chrt.fm/track/G8F1AF/pdrl.fm/c28362/injector.simplecastaudio.com/6fa1d34c-502b-4abf-bd82-483804006e0b/episodes/3120f4ea-faa3-4059-a9fc-d379e74302eb/audio/128/default.mp3?aid=rss_feed&awCollectionId=6fa1d34c-502b-4abf-bd82-483804006e0b&awEpisodeId=3120f4ea-faa3-4059-a9fc-d379e74302eb&feed=XA_851k3',1704256200,1402,0,656,0),
('5528640e-76ef-4ac6-bf20-54cccfed0f3e',450923,'Netlify CEO Matt Biilmann explains what we''ll see with UI 2.0',replace('<p>Biilmann says we can''t ignore the impact GenAI is having on developer productivity. ¬†One of their engineers created a ¬†GPT that automatically generates stories for React + TypeScript components, and after seeing how successful it was internally, Netlify <a href="https://storybook.js.org/blog/build-your-own-storybook-gpt/">made it open source for the public</a>.</p><p>We also chat over the results of their recent <a href="https://www.netlify.com/press/netlify-report-reveals-increased-adoption-of-composable-web-architecture/">State of Web Development</a> survey. The key takeaway is below:¬†</p><p><i>The 80% of developers that have integrated AI into their workflow are quickly reaping the benefits. Seventy percent report using AI to automate manual and repetitive tasks and 42% are using it to improve internal knowledge sharing and increase productivity, freeing up more time for impactful work and enabling faster launch times. Over 50% of developers also realized new opportunities that AI created, such as generating new web projects with a single prompt or reading API documentation.</i></p><p><i>However, AI experimentation is not without its own unique challenges. Developers are concerned about receiving incorrect answers and information (65%), security issues and leaking confidential information (52%), a lack of regulation (48%), and a decrease in code quality (45%).</i></p><p>So much opportunity, but plenty of risk as well.¬†</p><p>Last but not least, Biilmann tells us what he''s looking forward to in the near future, specifically apps that can reformat their UI on the fly to be more customized to each user. He calls this UI 2.0, and it sounds a bit like what Google showed off in its recent Gemini demo.¬†</p><p>Congrats to our lifeboat winner of the week, Petrus Theron, who answered the question: <a href="https://stackoverflow.com/questions/53866508/how-can-i-make-a-public-struct-where-all-fields-are-public-without-repeating-pu/53869723#53869723">How can I make a public struct where all fields are public without repeating `pub` for every field?</a></p>\n','\n',char(10)),'https://stackoverflow.blog/podcast/','https://chrt.fm/track/G8F1AF/pdrl.fm/c28362/injector.simplecastaudio.com/6fa1d34c-502b-4abf-bd82-483804006e0b/episodes/ba6da760-e24f-4a8b-b40a-cd79f288226b/audio/128/default.mp3?aid=rss_feed&awCollectionId=6fa1d34c-502b-4abf-bd82-483804006e0b&awEpisodeId=ba6da760-e24f-4a8b-b40a-cd79f288226b&feed=XA_851k3',1703216492,1462,0,655,0),
('c7a49920-d2fe-4dfa-8df0-fb6a2e7955f2',450923,'A tax change is hurting startups and developers',replace('<p>On today‚Äôs home team episode, Ben and Ryan discuss the implications of a lapse in section 174 of the tax code. Here‚Äôs <a href="https://gusto.com/resources/articles/taxes/section-174-r&d#:~:text=174%20explains%20how%20businesses%20should,or%20improvement%20of%20a%20product.">a great explainer</a> on how it‚Äôs affecting startups and software firms, threatening jobs and potentially bankrupting some struggling companies.¬†</p><p>Video game employees are exploring a union and <a href="https://www.nytimes.com/2023/12/12/business/economy/microsoft-unions.html">Microsoft recently announced</a> it will stay neutral in the process.¬†</p><p>What‚Äôs the difference between a bad game, a low effort developer, and <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Shovelware">shovelware</a>? Our game development Stack Exchange has <a href="https://gamedev.stackexchange.com/questions/154375/is-my-game-shovelware-if-it-uses-images-from-google-image-searches/154389#154389">some thoughts</a>.</p><p>Today‚Äôs lifeboat badge winner is ‚Äúthat_other_guy‚Äù, who explained: <a href="https://stackoverflow.com/questions/43724467/what-is-the-difference-between-kill-and-kill-9/43725403#43725403">What is the difference between kill and kill -9?</a> Hint, you want to terminate your process, not brutally murder it, ok!¬†</p>\n','\n',char(10)),'https://stackoverflow.blog/podcast/','https://chrt.fm/track/G8F1AF/pdrl.fm/c28362/injector.simplecastaudio.com/6fa1d34c-502b-4abf-bd82-483804006e0b/episodes/6a27a5aa-dddd-4327-805d-5ef6072c81d6/audio/128/default.mp3?aid=rss_feed&awCollectionId=6fa1d34c-502b-4abf-bd82-483804006e0b&awEpisodeId=6a27a5aa-dddd-4327-805d-5ef6072c81d6&feed=XA_851k3',1702986361,992,0,653,0),
('19a04476-4f22-4038-b0ee-be292f84d94f',450923,'From prompt attacks to data leaks, LLMs offer new capabilities and new threats',replace('<h2>SPONSORED BY DOIT</h2><p>The <a href="https://www.reddit.com/r/Scams/comments/11zqlu2/someone_just_called_my_dad_saying_it_was_me_and/">broken nose in jail scam</a> is on the rise. With AI improvements, it‚Äôll get harder to spot.¬†</p><p>OWASP, a non-profit dedicated to software security, tracks the <a href="https://owasp.org/www-project-top-10-for-large-language-model-applications/">top ten security risks for LLMs</a>.</p><p>We‚Äôve spoken with DoiT on the podcast before about <a href="https://stackoverflow.blog/2023/07/19/how-ai-can-help-your-business-without-the-hallucinations/">LLM hallucinations</a>.¬†</p><p><a href="https://www.doit.com/">DoiT</a>‚Äôs sales pitch is simple: they provide technology and expertise to clients who want to use the cloud, free of charge, with the big cloud providers paying the bills.</p>\n','\n',char(10)),'https://stackoverflow.blog/podcast/','https://chrt.fm/track/G8F1AF/pdrl.fm/c28362/injector.simplecastaudio.com/6fa1d34c-502b-4abf-bd82-483804006e0b/episodes/26c8a7cb-0e0b-44c1-856b-2389d9503d41/audio/128/default.mp3?aid=rss_feed&awCollectionId=6fa1d34c-502b-4abf-bd82-483804006e0b&awEpisodeId=26c8a7cb-0e0b-44c1-856b-2389d9503d41&feed=XA_851k3',1703085624,1457,0,654,0),
('cac79aa7-c807-4c50-96ae-41fb4c28b0f0',450923,'Can an AI get depressed?',replace('<p>Does ChatGPT have <a href="https://futurism.com/bizarre-theory-chatgpt-seasonal-depression">seasonal depression</a>?</p><p>AIs aren‚Äôt building apps on their own, at least not yet‚Äîbut they are helping developers build them. Read Isaac Lyman‚Äôs article about <a href="https://stackoverflow.blog/2023/12/11/three-types-of-ai-assisted-programmers/">the three types of AI-assisted programmers</a>.</p><p>ICYMI: Listen to <a href="https://stackoverflow.blog/2023/09/07/computers-are-learning-to-read-our-minds/">our interview with linguist Ga≈°per Begu≈°</a>, director of the Berkeley Speech and Computation Lab, about how LLMs and humans acquire language.¬†</p><p>Shoutout to Stack Overflow user <a href="https://stackoverflow.com/users/2792531/nhgrif">nhgrif</a>, who earned a <a href="https://stackoverflow.com/help/badges/8842/lifeboat">Lifeboat badge</a> by rescuing <a href="https://stackoverflow.com/questions/21218887/store-only-date-without-time-in-a-database">Store only date without time in a database</a> from the ash heap of history.</p>\n','\n',char(10)),'https://stackoverflow.blog/podcast/','https://chrt.fm/track/G8F1AF/pdrl.fm/c28362/injector.simplecastaudio.com/6fa1d34c-502b-4abf-bd82-483804006e0b/episodes/4b6cc598-d87c-4d95-a0a2-28a7ee9092fd/audio/128/default.mp3?aid=rss_feed&awCollectionId=6fa1d34c-502b-4abf-bd82-483804006e0b&awEpisodeId=4b6cc598-d87c-4d95-a0a2-28a7ee9092fd&feed=XA_851k3',1702617600,1078,0,652,0),
('16fbf725-2dce-44b5-8c05-9ab7ee38068a',450923,'Bringing context to alerting and incident management',replace('<h2>SPONSORED BY FIREHYDRANT</h2><p>While FireHydrant is mostly known for their incident management software, they‚Äôre introducing <a href="https://firehydrant.com/signals/?utm_source=stackoverflow&utm_medium=podcast&utm_campaign=signals">Signals</a> to modernize alerting and consolidate it with incident management.¬†</p><p>FireHydrant was born out of an incident where a database was dropped at 5:30pm on a Friday right before network maintenance started. It also led to Robert‚Äôs social media handle, <a href="https://xkcd.com/327/">Bobby Tables</a>.¬†</p><p>This one time‚Ä¶<a href="https://www.dci.org/">at band camp</a>‚Ä¶Robert got paged in the middle of trumpet practice‚Ä¶on his sabbatical.</p><p>Congrats to Great Question badge winner <a href="https://stackoverflow.com/users/1846736/timdim">timdim</a> for asking <a href="https://stackoverflow.com/questions/15197286/how-can-i-flush-gpu-memory-using-cuda-physical-reset-is-unavailable">How can I flush GPU memory using CUDA (physical reset is unavailable)</a>?. 100 people thought it was worth voting for.</p>\n','\n',char(10)),'https://stackoverflow.blog/podcast/','https://chrt.fm/track/G8F1AF/pdrl.fm/c28362/injector.simplecastaudio.com/6fa1d34c-502b-4abf-bd82-483804006e0b/episodes/51a5c4ab-0822-497b-930c-56dce275731a/audio/128/default.mp3?aid=rss_feed&awCollectionId=6fa1d34c-502b-4abf-bd82-483804006e0b&awEpisodeId=51a5c4ab-0822-497b-930c-56dce275731a&feed=XA_851k3',1702444800,1348,0,651,0),
('c9a7464b-6ddd-4d2d-8c8d-a6844cc9711f',450923,'What Gemini means for the GenAI boom',replace('<p><a href="https://deepmind.google/technologies/gemini/#introduction">Gemini</a>, Google‚Äôs new AI model, is great at <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=LvGmVmHv69s&t=15s&ab_channel=Google">competitive programming</a>, among <a href="https://twitter.com/sundarpichai/status/1732433036929589301">other things</a>.</p><p><a href="https://www.youtube.com/@aiexplained-official">AI Explained</a> is a YouTube channel that covers the latest developments in AI.</p><p>One problem with <a href="https://www.nytimes.com/2023/12/06/technology/ai-regulation-policies.html">regulating AI</a> is that the technology evolves (much) faster than regulators can.</p><p><a href="https://www.wikifunctions.org/wiki/Wikifunctions:About">Wikifunctions</a> is an open repository of code that anyone can use or contribute to.</p><p>Did we need another study to tell us that longer commutes are bad for mental health? Probably not, but <a href="https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/S2214140523001676">here‚Äôs one</a> anyway.</p><p>Are governments spying on you through push notifications? <a href="https://www.reuters.com/technology/cybersecurity/governments-spying-apple-google-users-through-push-notifications-us-senator-2023-12-06/">Sounds like it</a>! In fact, push notifications are a <a href="https://blog.davidlibeau.fr/push-notifications-are-a-privacy-nightmare/">privacy nightmare</a>.</p>\n','\n',char(10)),'https://stackoverflow.blog/podcast/','https://chrt.fm/track/G8F1AF/pdrl.fm/c28362/injector.simplecastaudio.com/6fa1d34c-502b-4abf-bd82-483804006e0b/episodes/c521960a-f18c-43c0-b3af-f22f7fb9ad43/audio/128/default.mp3?aid=rss_feed&awCollectionId=6fa1d34c-502b-4abf-bd82-483804006e0b&awEpisodeId=c521960a-f18c-43c0-b3af-f22f7fb9ad43&feed=XA_851k3',1702358400,1273,0,650,0),
('796f3e76-25fa-43e8-84d5-4babab7deea1',450923,'One weird trick for teaching users your software',replace('<p><a href="https://www.commandbar.com/">CommandBar</a> is a user assistance platform (UAP). Their flagship product, <a href="https://www.commandbar.com/copilot/">Copilot</a>, is an embedded user assistant agent that companies can configure to help their users with on-demand help, including interactive walkthroughs and personalized responses.¬†</p><p>Read James‚Äôs article about <a href="https://www.commandbar.com/blog/why-we-built-copilot/">why CommandBar built Copilot</a>, then get started with their <a href="https://www.commandbar.com/docs/guides/getting-started/commandbar-manifesto-decoded/">docs</a>.</p><p>Follow James on <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/james-evans-7086b3126/">LinkedIn</a> and <a href="https://twitter.com/dazzeloid">Twitter</a>.</p><p>Follow CommandBar on <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/company/commandbar">LinkedIn</a> and <a href="https://twitter.com/CommandBar">Twitter</a>.</p><p>If you‚Äôve ever wondered <a href="https://stackoverflow.com/questions/69019854/why-is-yarn-2-yarn-3-0-1">Why "Yarn 2" is Yarn 3.0.1</a>, <a href="https://stackoverflow.com/help/badges/8842/lifeboat">Lifeboat badge</a> winner <a href="https://stackoverflow.com/users/414415/ilias-karim">Ilias Karim</a> has your answer.</p>\n','\n',char(10)),'https://stackoverflow.blog/podcast/','https://chrt.fm/track/G8F1AF/pdrl.fm/c28362/injector.simplecastaudio.com/6fa1d34c-502b-4abf-bd82-483804006e0b/episodes/8a65ea53-a449-4d8f-bebb-8c69e3a85c28/audio/128/default.mp3?aid=rss_feed&awCollectionId=6fa1d34c-502b-4abf-bd82-483804006e0b&awEpisodeId=8a65ea53-a449-4d8f-bebb-8c69e3a85c28&feed=XA_851k3',1702012800,1816,0,649,0),
('298b53f3-1f5f-4ceb-8177-5b8610618d77',450923,'Are LLMs the end of computer programming (as we know it)?',replace('<p>Do LLMs herald <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=JhCl-GeT4jw&ab_channel=CS50">the end of computer programming</a> (as we know it)? A Harvard lecture weighs in on this contentious topic.</p><p>An epic <a href="https://www.gamedeveloper.com/programming/my-hardest-bug-ever">hardware bug story</a>.</p><p>Question from the academic trenches: How bad will it look to prospective employers if you <a href="https://academia.stackexchange.com/questions/204301/how-bad-will-refusing-to-defend-phd-look-on-industry-job-applications">refuse to defend your PhD</a>? (Answer: Pretty bad.)</p><p>Another intriguing question: Were postal pneumatic tubes in Berlin <a href="https://skeptics.stackexchange.com/questions/56383/were-postal-pneumatic-tubes-in-berlin-rohrpost-cleared-with-wine">really cleaned with wine</a>?</p><p>The Jetsons misled us about many aspects of the future, from flying cars to the role of pneumatics, but they were onto something with the <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Series_of_tubes">series of tubes</a>.</p><p>Before influencers and social media algorithms, there were <a href="https://www.tucsonweekly.com/tucson/coolhunting/Content?oid=1071857">coolhunters</a>.</p><p>Congrats to Stack Overflow user <a href="https://stackoverflow.com/users/2321643/tjati">tjati</a>, who earned a <a href="https://stackoverflow.com/help/badges/8842/lifeboat">Lifeboat badge</a> by answering <a href="https://stackoverflow.com/questions/23995697/what-does-html-is-escaping-mean">What does ''HTML is escaping'' mean?</a>.</p>\n','\n',char(10)),'https://stackoverflow.blog/podcast/','https://chrt.fm/track/G8F1AF/pdrl.fm/c28362/injector.simplecastaudio.com/6fa1d34c-502b-4abf-bd82-483804006e0b/episodes/c4dc5ee0-80bb-4d62-9791-4ed952ddd825/audio/128/default.mp3?aid=rss_feed&awCollectionId=6fa1d34c-502b-4abf-bd82-483804006e0b&awEpisodeId=c4dc5ee0-80bb-4d62-9791-4ed952ddd825&feed=XA_851k3',1701753600,1327,0,648,0),
('1732c1e1-9bed-44e0-a709-9a72d3f38744',450923,'Will developers return to hostile offices?',replace('<p>As the year winds to a close, some big employers are facing <a href="https://www.wsj.com/business/the-new-headache-for-bosses-employees-arent-quitting-edca96a3?mod=hp_lead_pos1">lower-than-expected attrition rates</a>‚Äîin other words, fewer people than expected are quitting. What a difference a year or two makes.</p><p>People have <a href="https://benjiweber.co.uk/blog/2023/11/12/tragedy-of-return-to-hostile-offices/">strong opinions</a> on the return-to-office conversation. Read Eira‚Äôs <a href="https://stackoverflow.blog/2023/11/27/are-remote-workers-more-productive-that-s-the-wrong-question/">article</a> and let us know how you feel.</p><p>We are just beginning to explore the effects of prompting on the <a href="https://jxnl.github.io/instructor/blog/2023/11/05/chain-of-density/">capabilities and performance</a> of LLMs.</p><p>The <a href="https://arstechnica.com/gadgets/2023/11/humane-ai-pin-a-700-voice-command-box-definitely-wont-replace-your-phone/">Humane AI pin</a> can be described as a cross between two of humanity‚Äôs most beloved technologies: Google Glass and the pager.</p><p>People are using low-cost drones, 3D printers, and private satellites to preserve irreplaceable <a href="https://singularityhub.com/2023/11/06/a-revolution-in-computer-graphics-is-bringing-3d-reality-capture-to-the-masses/">cultural heritage sites</a> before they are destroyed or lost to time. (Stay tuned while Eira figures out how to apply this tech as a <a href="https://www.instagram.com/quietneighbors/?hl=en">cemetery tour guide</a>.)</p><p>Stack Overflow user <a href="https://stackoverflow.com/users/1394697/flipperpa">FlipperPA</a> earned a <a href="https://stackoverflow.com/help/badges/8842/lifeboat">Lifeboat badge</a> with their answer to <a href="https://stackoverflow.com/questions/64530101/the-black-formatter-python">The ''Black'' formatter - Python</a>.</p>\n','\n',char(10)),'https://stackoverflow.blog/podcast/','https://chrt.fm/track/G8F1AF/pdrl.fm/c28362/injector.simplecastaudio.com/6fa1d34c-502b-4abf-bd82-483804006e0b/episodes/2df79274-24d9-4cbe-b0d0-ce2e82afb7e7/audio/128/default.mp3?aid=rss_feed&awCollectionId=6fa1d34c-502b-4abf-bd82-483804006e0b&awEpisodeId=2df79274-24d9-4cbe-b0d0-ce2e82afb7e7&feed=XA_851k3',1701408000,1105,0,647,0),
('61c0a9b2-e2c7-4611-ab66-0e79e8c863a7',450923,'Can GenAI 10X developer productivity?',replace('<p><a href="https://bito.ai/">Bito AI</a> is an AI coding tool that helps developers work more productively with features like <a href="https://bito.ai/product/ai-code-completions/">code completion</a> within the IDE and <a href="https://bito.ai/product/ai-for-coding/">personalized answers</a> drawn from your codebase. Get started with their docs <a href="https://docs.bito.ai/?_gl=1*10pjowv*_gcl_au*MjA3MzA0Nzc0Mi4xNzAxMTAyNjYz">here</a>.</p><p>ICYMI: <a href="https://stackoverflow.blog/2023/10/18/retrieval-augmented-generation-keeping-llms-relevant-and-current/">Retrieval augmented generation (RAG)</a> is a way of addressing LLM hallucinations and outdated training data.</p><p>Listen to our recent episode about how an original architect of Jira is rethinking <a href="https://stackoverflow.blog/2023/11/07/he-helped-create-jira-now-he-s-searching-for-meaningful-engineering-metrics/">meaningful engineering metrics</a>.</p><p>Connect with Anand on <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/ananddas/">LinkedIn</a> or <a href="https://twitter.com/ananddas">Twitter.com</a>.¬†</p><p>Shoutout to Stack Overflow user¬†</p><p><a href="https://stackoverflow.com/users/7589596/jan-karda%c5%a1">Jan Karda≈°</a>, whose answer to <a href="https://stackoverflow.com/questions/26916952/go-retrieve-a-string-from-between-two-characters-or-other-strings">Go: Retrieve a string from between two characters or other strings</a> earned them a <a href="https://stackoverflow.com/help/badges/8842/lifeboat">Lifeboat badge</a>.</p>\n','\n',char(10)),'https://stackoverflow.blog/podcast/','https://chrt.fm/track/G8F1AF/pdrl.fm/c28362/injector.simplecastaudio.com/6fa1d34c-502b-4abf-bd82-483804006e0b/episodes/446d4bb3-b051-4c03-8e44-e842561e5e8a/audio/128/default.mp3?aid=rss_feed&awCollectionId=6fa1d34c-502b-4abf-bd82-483804006e0b&awEpisodeId=446d4bb3-b051-4c03-8e44-e842561e5e8a&feed=XA_851k3',1701148800,1930,0,646,0