('3dc7cdad-b6ac-4b19-adf5-d4122215ce3e',450923,'Build vs. buy doesn''t matter. Tool adoption does.',replace('<h2>SPONSORED BY CHRONOSPHERE</h2><p>Episode notes:</p><p>Chronosphere is introducing <a href="https://chronosphere.io/learn/empower-developer-effectiveness-in-the-cloud-native-age-with-chronosphere-lens/">Lens</a>, a cloud-native observability tool to view data flows between services.¬†</p><p>At Uber, Rob created <a href="https://m3db.io/">M3</a>, an open-source metrics engine compatible with Prometheus.¬†¬†</p><p>Congrats to Lifeboat badge winner, <a href="https://stackoverflow.com/users/5230735/ralf-htp">ralf htp</a>, for their answer to <a href="https://stackoverflow.com/questions/46540831/how-to-read-an-image-in-python-opencv/46542343#46542343">How to read an image in Python OpenCV</a>.¬†</p><p>If you want to meet Rob and the Chronosphere team, they‚Äôll be at <a href="https://reinvent.awsevents.com/">AWS re:Invent¬†</a> from Nov. 27 to Dec. 1.</p>\n','\n',char(10)),'https://stackoverflow.blog/podcast/','https://chrt.fm/track/G8F1AF/pdrl.fm/c28362/injector.simplecastaudio.com/6fa1d34c-502b-4abf-bd82-483804006e0b/episodes/68e8dae5-c84c-4593-a5ad-ee40d8184950/audio/128/default.mp3?aid=rss_feed&awCollectionId=6fa1d34c-502b-4abf-bd82-483804006e0b&awEpisodeId=68e8dae5-c84c-4593-a5ad-ee40d8184950&feed=XA_851k3',1700025600,1635,0,642,0),
('1a4b032c-5268-4617-8771-b3e6e81fb993',450923,'How the cocreator of Kubernetes is helping developers build safer software',replace('<p><a href="https://stacklok.com/">Stacklok</a> helps developers and open-source communities build safer software, secure the supply chain, and choose safer dependencies. <a href="https://stacklok.com/trusty">Trusty</a> is their free-to-use service that employs a statistical analysis of author/repo activity and a package‚Äôs source of origin to assess its trustworthiness.</p><p>Craig cofounded the <a href="https://kubernetes.io/">Kubernetes</a> project, an open-source system for automating deployment, scaling, and management of containerized applications.</p><p>He is also the former VP of Research and Development at <a href="https://www.vmware.com/">VMWare</a>.</p><p>Follow Craig on <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/craigmcluckie/">LinkedIn</a>.</p><p>Congrats to Stack Overflow user <a href="https://stackoverflow.com/users/14645616/netcorefan">netcorefan</a>, who earned a <a href="https://stackoverflow.com/help/badges/8842/lifeboat">Lifeboat badge</a> with their answer to <a href="https://stackoverflow.com/questions/66379248/need-a-workaround-to-access-readonlyspant-inside-a-function-that-returns-an-ie">Need a workaround to access ReadOnlySpan<T> inside a function that returns an IEnumerable</a>.</p>\n','\n',char(10)),'https://stackoverflow.blog/podcast/','https://chrt.fm/track/G8F1AF/pdrl.fm/c28362/injector.simplecastaudio.com/6fa1d34c-502b-4abf-bd82-483804006e0b/episodes/b579ad3f-ce2b-4b88-bee8-0a3a6ce5369d/audio/128/default.mp3?aid=rss_feed&awCollectionId=6fa1d34c-502b-4abf-bd82-483804006e0b&awEpisodeId=b579ad3f-ce2b-4b88-bee8-0a3a6ce5369d&feed=XA_851k3',1699593600,966,0,640,0),
('e5bde084-e359-4e40-91cf-32f8f2052f6f',450923,'Trust as a service for validating OSS dependencies',replace('<p>ICYMI, listen to <a href="https://stackoverflow.blog/2023/11/10/how-the-cocreator-of-kubernetes-is-helping-developers-build-safer-software/">part one</a> of this conversation.</p><p>Craig is the cofounder and CEO of <a href="https://stacklok.com/">Stacklok</a>, which helps developers and open-source communities build safer software, secure the supply chain, and choose safer dependencies. Stacklok‚Äôs free-to-use service, <a href="https://stacklok.com/trusty">Trusty</a>, employs a statistical analysis of author/repo activity and a package‚Äôs source of origin to assess its trustworthiness.</p><p>Craig cofounded the <a href="https://kubernetes.io/">Kubernetes</a> project, an open-source system for automating deployment, scaling, and management of containerized applications.</p><p>Craig is on <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/craigmcluckie/">LinkedIn</a>.</p><p>Stack Overflow user <a href="https://stackoverflow.com/users/1281407/mprivat">mprivat</a> earned a well-deserved <a href="https://stackoverflow.com/help/badges/8842/lifeboat">Lifeboat badge</a> by answering <a href="https://stackoverflow.com/questions/33682403/abstract-class-extending-concrete-classes">Abstract class extending concrete classes</a>.</p>\n','\n',char(10)),'https://stackoverflow.blog/podcast/','https://chrt.fm/track/G8F1AF/pdrl.fm/c28362/injector.simplecastaudio.com/6fa1d34c-502b-4abf-bd82-483804006e0b/episodes/33128652-016d-4a5d-a5e7-3ee9869f8a3f/audio/128/default.mp3?aid=rss_feed&awCollectionId=6fa1d34c-502b-4abf-bd82-483804006e0b&awEpisodeId=33128652-016d-4a5d-a5e7-3ee9869f8a3f&feed=XA_851k3',1699939200,769,0,641,0),
('a9ebc1fd-2ed4-421b-b3cd-750ab76e3c40',450923,'He helped create Jira. Now he''s searching for meaningful engineering metrics',replace('<p><a href="https://www.sleuth.io/">Sleuth</a> helps engineering teams systematically improve efficiency by tracking speed and release quality, preventing slowdowns and bottlenecks, and removing toil and unnecessary friction. <a href="https://app.sleuth.io/account/signup/">Try it for free</a> or see <a href="https://www.sleuth.io/resources/real-world-stories/">how teams are using Sleuth</a>. Interested in the automations they offer for teams, check out their <a href="https://marketplace.sleuth.io./">public marketplace</a>.</p><p>Dylan was an original architect on <a href="https://www.atlassian.com/software/jira">JIRA</a>, so he‚Äôs not exactly new to issue- and project-tracking software.</p><p><a href="https://dora.dev/">DevOps Research and Assessment (DORA)</a> is a research program that tries to understand what drives successful software delivery and operations performance.¬†</p><p>According to Dylan, one thing the best development teams have in common is their culture of <a href="https://resources.stackoverflow.co/topic/thought-leadership/prioritize-learning/">continuous learning</a>.</p><p>Connect with Dylan on <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/dylanetkin/">LinkedIn</a>.</p>\n','\n',char(10)),'https://stackoverflow.blog/podcast/','https://chrt.fm/track/G8F1AF/pdrl.fm/c28362/injector.simplecastaudio.com/6fa1d34c-502b-4abf-bd82-483804006e0b/episodes/e3e49436-524f-4a1c-8f78-4ea3d0e195c1/audio/128/default.mp3?aid=rss_feed&awCollectionId=6fa1d34c-502b-4abf-bd82-483804006e0b&awEpisodeId=e3e49436-524f-4a1c-8f78-4ea3d0e195c1&feed=XA_851k3',1699334400,1729,0,639,0),
