('3862c69d-48f2-40c2-8a8d-4554b691a863',450923,'USB-C for all, PHP 4EVA, and what do LLMs actually know (if anything)?',replace('<p>Ben is watching <a href="https://www.youtube.com/@aiexplained-official">AI Explained</a>, a YouTube channel that covers the latest AI developments and their implications.¬†</p><p>Read Ryan‚Äôs article ‚Äã‚Äã<a href="https://stackoverflow.blog/2023/07/03/do-large-language-models-know-what-they-are-talking-about/">Do large language models know what they are talking about?</a>.</p><p>Is language really unique to humans? <a href="https://www.nytimes.com/2023/09/20/magazine/animal-communication.html">New research</a> suggests maybe not.</p><p>Not for the first time, Ryan recommends the work of Noam Chomsky: <a href="https://www.amazon.com/Why-Only-Us-Language-Evolution/dp/0262533499"><i>Why Only Us: Language and Evolution</i></a>, an evolutionary account of language acquisition in humans written with Robert C. Berwick.</p><p>OverflowAI search is now available for alpha testing. Learn more <a href="https://meta.stackoverflow.com/questions/426432/overflowai-search-is-now-available-for-alpha-testing-september-13-2023">here</a>.</p><p>Good news for your cable clutter: <a href="https://www.bloomberg.com/news/newsletters/2023-09-03/apple-september-12-event-iphone-15-charging-port-change-to-usb-c-from-lightning-lm3gn2hs">Apple is switching</a> to USB-C charging ports. Here‚Äôs <a href="https://www.macworld.com/article/1341317/lightning-usb-c-iphone-ipad-airpods-magic-mouse-earpods.html">when</a>.</p><p>The WGA (Writers Guild of America) strike ended with an agreement that ‚Äú<a href="https://www.theguardian.com/culture/2023/oct/01/hollywood-writers-strike-artificial-intelligence">allows for artificial intelligence as a tool, not a replacement</a>,‚Äù but the arguments about creativity, copyright, and AI are <a href="https://gizmodo.com/ai-this-week-the-hollywood-writers-strike-may-have-end-1850877755">far from over</a>.</p><p>If you‚Äôre interested in working with PHP, head over to the <a href="https://stackoverflow.com/collectives/php">PHP Collective</a> and check out conversations like <a href="https://stackoverflow.com/collectives/php/beta/discussions/77084357/most-useful-new-php-features-for-version-8">Most useful new PHP features for version 8?</a>.</p>\n','\n',char(10)),'https://stackoverflow.blog/podcast/','https://chrt.fm/track/G8F1AF/pdrl.fm/c28362/injector.simplecastaudio.com/6fa1d34c-502b-4abf-bd82-483804006e0b/episodes/a469f829-aa2d-4b62-a024-c7f15fde6f5e/audio/128/default.mp3?aid=rss_feed&awCollectionId=6fa1d34c-502b-4abf-bd82-483804006e0b&awEpisodeId=a469f829-aa2d-4b62-a024-c7f15fde6f5e&feed=XA_851k3',1696306800,1083,0,627,0),
('a4b86b56-fa95-4183-a720-8de179eb93a1',450923,'How to write high-performance SQL for your Postgres database',replace('<p><a href="https://pganalyze.com/">pgnanalyze</a> helps users deliver consistent <a href="https://www.postgresql.org/">PostgreSQL</a> performance and availability at any scale. Get started with a <a href="https://app.pganalyze.com/users/sign_up">free trial</a> or explore their <a href="https://pganalyze.com/docs">docs</a>. You can also find them on YouTube, where Lukas posts a weekly show called <a href="https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCDV_1Dz2Ixgl1nT_3DUZVFw">5mins of Postgres</a>.</p><p>Lukas was a founding engineer of <a href="https://www.citusdata.com/">Citus Data</a>. Citus is an open-source extension to PostgreSQL that was eventually acquired by Microsoft. Find them on <a href="https://github.com/citusdata/citus">GitHub</a>.</p><p>If you‚Äôre new to the topic, <a href="https://stackoverflow.blog/2017/11/16/developers-can-build-sql-skills/">SQL (Structured Query Language)</a> is a language for querying databases, introduced in the 1970s.¬†</p><p>Find Lukas on <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/lfittl/">LinkedIn</a>, <a href="https://twitter.com/LukasFittl">Twitter</a>, or <a href="https://github.com/lfittl">GitHub</a>.</p>\n','\n',char(10)),'https://stackoverflow.blog/podcast/','https://chrt.fm/track/G8F1AF/pdrl.fm/c28362/injector.simplecastaudio.com/6fa1d34c-502b-4abf-bd82-483804006e0b/episodes/280a2b5c-eca5-43b9-98b7-aa8d847154ad/audio/128/default.mp3?aid=rss_feed&awCollectionId=6fa1d34c-502b-4abf-bd82-483804006e0b&awEpisodeId=280a2b5c-eca5-43b9-98b7-aa8d847154ad&feed=XA_851k3',1695961200,1484,0,626,0),
('49d4cc07-52a8-4270-9965-a892bdd1aeda',450923,'Being creative with math: The immersive artist who traded a sketchpad for a keyboard',replace('<p>Check out Luyang‚Äôs work at his <a href="https://luyangzou.com/">website</a> or in this <a href="https://www.youtube.com/@LABZOU">Youtube playlist</a>.¬†</p><p>To make these animations, Luyang uses <a href="https://processing.org/">Processing</a>, a 20-year-old language that started out as a visual way to teach programming but evolved into a professional development tool.¬†</p><p>Logitech selected Luyang as one of the ambassadors to show off what you can do with their <a href="https://www.logitech.com/en-us/products/combos/mx-keys-s-keyboard-mouse-combo.html">MX Keys S Combo</a>.¬†</p><p>Shout out to <a href="https://stackoverflow.com/users/89766/george-profenza">George Profenza</a> for dropping a top answer on <a href="https://stackoverflow.com/questions/76793291/position-of-a-vector-in-coordinate-system-processing-p5-js/76814353#76814353">Position of a vector in coordinate system (Processing/p5.js)</a>.</p>\n','\n',char(10)),'https://stackoverflow.blog/podcast/','https://chrt.fm/track/G8F1AF/pdrl.fm/c28362/injector.simplecastaudio.com/6fa1d34c-502b-4abf-bd82-483804006e0b/episodes/6fb47b81-ded9-428e-8399-2a05384f05cc/audio/128/default.mp3?aid=rss_feed&awCollectionId=6fa1d34c-502b-4abf-bd82-483804006e0b&awEpisodeId=6fb47b81-ded9-428e-8399-2a05384f05cc&feed=XA_851k3',1695788400,1428,0,625,0),
